INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3700','letter','1780-06-23','Bryants Tavern','PA','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','I now acquaint you that they proceeded, with vigor, until they had gained Connecticut Farms ; they then were checked by Colonel Dayton\'s regiment.','ltr_nag3700.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3701','letter','1780-06-24','Springfield','PA','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','the whole force of the enemy, which has been in Jersey, went from Elizabethtown Point between twelve and one o\'clock this morning.','ltr_nag3701.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3702','letter','1780-08-03','Verplancks Point','NY','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','To explain the reasons for the movement will give the army a high opinion of the confidence you have in their spirit and enterprise, and perfectly reconcile them to all the past fatigues, and to those which may follow','ltr_nag3702.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3703','letter','1780-08-05','Verplancks Point','NY','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','I am sensible my conduct has been viewed by many in a very improper light; and I am persuaded many think the business can be done with more method, and at a less expense, than it has been.','ltr_nag3703.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3704','letter','1780-10-05','','','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','A new disposition of the army going to be made, and an officer appointed to the command of West Point and the district on the east side of the North River, I take the liberty just to intimate my inclinations for the appointment.','ltr_nag3704.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3705','letter','1780-10-16','West Point','NY','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','Your Excellency\'s letter of the 14th, appointing me to the command of the Southern army, was delivered me last evening.','ltr_nag3705.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3706','letter','1780-10-31','Philadelphia','PA','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','On my arrival at this place, I laid your Excellency\'s letter before Congress, and addressed them on the business of the Southern department.','ltr_nag3706.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3707','letter','1780-11-03','Philadelphia','PA','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','The arms we are likely to get from the Board of War and this State fall far short of my expectations. The whole will not exceed fifteen hundred.','ltr_nag3707.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3708','letter','1780-11-19','Richmond','VA','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','Your weight and influence, both with Congress and this State, in support of the southern operations, will be exceedingly important and necessary to my success.','ltr_nag3708.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3709','letter','1780-12-28','Cheraw','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','I was apprehensive, on my first arrival, that the country around Charlotte was too much exhausted to afford subsistence for the army at that place for any considerable time.','ltr_nag3709.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3710','letter','1781-01-13','Pedee','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','This country is so extensive, and supplies are so difficult to obtain, that it is impossible to carry on the war any length of time with the militia.','ltr_nag3710.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3711','letter','1781-01-24','Pedee','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','My public letter will inform your Excellency of the success of the troops under the command of General Morgan. The event is glorious ; and I am exceedingly unhappy that our wretched condition will not permit our improving it to the best advantage.','ltr_nag3711.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3712','letter','1781-01-28','Pedee','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','Lord Cornwallis continued at Weymsborough, making every preparation, and completely equipping his troops for the most active operations, until the 9th instant','ltr_nag3712.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3713','letter','1781-02-09','Guilford','NC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','Since I wrote your Excellency by Major Giles, Lord Cornwallis has been constantly in pursuit of the light infantry and the prisoners, and is now between the Shallow Ford, upon the Yadkin and Salem, one of the Moravian towns','ltr_nag3713.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3714','letter','1781-02-15','Irwins Ferry','','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','Lord Cornwallis has been at our heels from day to day ever since we left Guilford; and our movements from thence to this place have been of the most critical kind, having a river in our front, and the enemy in our rear.','ltr_nag3714.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3715','letter','1781-02-28','High Rock Ford','','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','We have the most unequivocal and full evidence of the disaffection of a great part of this State. The enemy have raised seven independent companies in a single day; and we have the mortification to find, that most of the prisoners we take are inhabitants of America.','ltr_nag3715.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3716','letter','1781-03-10','Iron Works','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','On the 2d, Lieutenant-Colonel Lee, with a detachment of riflemen, attacked the advance of the British army under Colonel Tarleton, near Alamanee, and killed and wounded, by report, about thirty of them.','ltr_nag3716.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3717','letter','1781-03-18','Iron Works','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','My letter to Congress, a copy of which I inclose to your Excellency, will inform you of an unsuccessful action with Lord Cornwallis on the 15th. Our prospects were flattering ; and had the North Carolina militia seconded the endeavours of their officers, victory was certain.','ltr_nag3717.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3718','letter','1781-03-29','Deep River','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','an account from Richmond, of Admiral Arbuthnot\'s arriving in the Chesapeake, with six ships of the line and upwards of thirty transports, with a considerable reenforcement.','ltr_nag3718.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3719','letter','1781-05-14','Mccords Ferry','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','They left it with great precipitation, after burning the greater part of their baggage, and stores belonging to the inhabitants. They also burnt the jail, mill, and several other houses, and left the town little better than a heap of rubbish.','ltr_nag3719.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3720','letter','1781-06-22','Bush River','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','We are anxiously waiting the arrival of the second division of the French fleet. Virginia affords the most inviting object.','ltr_nag3720.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3721','letter','1781-07-17','Santee','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','It affords me great pleasure to hear that an attack is meditating against New York. This measure no doubt will create a powerful diversion in favor of this country','ltr_nag3721.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3722','letter','1781-08-06','Santee','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','Governor Rutledge arrived in camp a few days since, and informed me that a French fleet of twenty sail of the line, besides frigates, were to be on the coast by the 25th of this month, to cooperate with the American army','ltr_nag3722.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3723','letter','1781-08-26','Camden','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','the hanging of Colonel Hayne, one of our militia Colonels, whom the enemy hung in Charleston, a little time since, as a traitor, as they call him.','ltr_nag3723.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3724','letter','1781-09-17','Santee','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','Since I wrote to you before, we have had a most bloody battle. It was by far the most obstinate fight I ever saw. Victory was ours','ltr_nag3724.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3725','letter','1781-10-25','Santee','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','I am happy to find the army under your command ready to commence operations against Lord Cornwallis ; but I am sorry to hear you think the issue somewhat doubtful.','ltr_nag3725.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3726','letter','1781-11-21','','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','The reduction of Charleston is an event much to be wished ; but to be able to cover the country and confine the enemy to that place, will be a great object.','ltr_nag3726.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3727','letter','1782-01-21','St. Pauls Parish','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','Through a good channel of intelligence I got information of troops expected, both from Cork and New York. I was so alarmed at it, that I sent off Captain Ragsdale to Virginia, and Lieutenant-Colonel Stewart to North Carolina, to try to hasten on support','ltr_nag3727.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3728','letter','1782-02-07','St. Pauls Parish','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','my apprehensions were so great, and the consequences appeared to me so fatal to this country, I made application, without hesitation','ltr_nag3728.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3729','letter','1782-03-09','Ponpon','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','Your Excellency will see by the King\'s speech, and other measures taking in Great Britain, the enemy are determined to prosecute the war','ltr_nag3729.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3730','letter','1782-05-19','','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','Count de Grasse is a prisoner, and has lost six ships of the line; and I fear the rest of the fleet are so shattered as to be incapable of attempting any thing for a long time.','ltr_nag3730.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3731','letter','1782-08-29','Ashley Hill','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','Since I wrote to your Excellency, a day or two ago, Lieutenant-Colonel Laurens has been killed in an action on the Combahee River, about fifty miles south of our camp.','ltr_nag3731.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3732','letter','1782-10-04','Ashley Hill','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','the evacuation of Charleston is reduced to a certainty. The following disposition, it is said, is to be made of the troops in garrison.','ltr_nag3732.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3733','letter','1780-12-07','Camp Charlotte','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','Immediately I called a Council, respecting the practicability of holding a Council of Inquiry upon General Gates\'s conduct, during his command in this department.','ltr_nag3733.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3734','letter','1782-12-10','Ashley Hill','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','I doubt not your Excellency expected to hear of the evacuation of Charleston long before this. The enemy are not yet gone, although now just upon the eve of their departure. In two days more, the town will be free.','ltr_nag3734.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3735','letter','1781-05-01','','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','We fight, get beat and fight again. We have so much to do and so little to do it with, that I am much afraid these States must fall, never to rise again','ltr_nag3735.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3736','letter','1782-07-11','Ashley River','SC','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','The troops have been so badly clothed, and the season is so very hot, that many of the soldiery have been seized with fevers, which renders them unfit for service','ltr_nag3736.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_nag3737','letter','1780-10-19','West Point','NY','US','Nathanael','Greene','','George','Washington','','individual','','I had given over the thoughts of going home, even if I obtained your permission, before I received your pleasure upon the subject. My affairs require it ; but I am fully convinced that the time it will take, and the state of the Southern department','ltr_nag3737.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
